### VS Code REST Client friendly tests
@base=http://localhost:8000

### 1) Health
GET {{base}}/health

### 2) Register (choose your email)
POST {{base}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### 3) Who am I? (should reflect the cookie from register/login)
GET {{base}}/auth/me

### 4) Logout
POST {{base}}/auth/logout

### 5) Login
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@example.com",
  "password": "secret123"
}

### 6) List my documents
GET {{base}}/documents

### 7) Upload a file
POST {{base}}/ingest/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

# (Use your REST client to attach a file field named 'files')

### 8) Stream generate (SSE)
# Open this in a browser/new tab to watch server-sent events
GET {{base}}/ingest/stream_generate?doc_id=1
